<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<theorem xmlns="Theorem"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         type="Corollary"
         id="Thm_DoubleOrthogonalComplementGivesSpan"
         xsi:schemaLocation="Theorem file:/C:/xampp/htdocs/moodle/mod/msm/NewSchemas/Theorem.xsd">
   <caption>Double orthogonal complement gives span</caption>
   <statement.theorem>
      <para>
         <para.body>Given a subset <math>
               <latex>S</latex>
            </math> of a subvector space <math>
               <latex>W</latex>
            </math> of <math>
               <latex>\RNr[n]</latex>
            </math>,</para.body>
      </para>
      <math.array column="3">
         <row rowspan="1">
            <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
               <math>
                  <latex>S^{\bot\bot}</latex>
               </math>
            </cell>
            <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
               <math>
                  <latex>=</latex>
               </math>
            </cell>
            <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
               <math>
                  <latex>\span(S)</latex>
               </math>
            </cell>
         </row>
      </math.array>
   </statement.theorem>
   <proof type="Proof">
      <proof.block>
         <para>
            <para.body>To verify the equality of the two subspaces of <math>
                  <latex>\RNr[n]</latex>
               </math>, we need to verify two inclusions:</para.body>
         </para>
         <ul>
            <li>
               <para>
                  <para.body>
                     <math>
                        <latex>S^{\bot\bot}\subseteq \span(S)</latex>
                     </math>
                  </para.body>
               </para>
            </li>
            <li>
               <para>
                  <para.body>
                     <math>
                        <latex>\span(S)\subseteq S^{\bot\bot}</latex>
                     </math>
                  </para.body>
               </para>
            </li>
         </ul>
         <caption>
            <math>
               <latex>S^{\bot\bot}\subseteq \span(S)</latex>
            </math>
         </caption>
         <para>
            <para.body>To see that <math>
                  <latex>S^{\bot\bot}=\span(S)=:V</latex>
               </math>, 
			<subordinate>
                  <hot>recall</hot>
                  <crossref>
                     <theorem.ref theoremID="Thm_OrthogonalComplementOperationProperties"/>
                     <info>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>Review this fact</para.body>
                        </para>
                     </info>
                  </crossref>
               </subordinate>
			that <math>
                  <latex>S^{\bot}=V^{\bot}</latex>
               </math>. Therefore, we may equivalently show that <math>
                  <latex>V^{\bot\bot}=V</latex>
               </math>. Now, if
<math>
                  <latex>\Vect{x}\in V^{\bot\bot}</latex>
               </math>, write</para.body>
         </para>
         <math.array column="3">
            <row rowspan="1">
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>\Vect{x}</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>=</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>\Vect{x}_V + \Vect{x}_{\bot}</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
            </row>
         </math.array>
         <para>
            <para.body>with <math>
                  <latex>\Vect{x}_V\in V</latex>
               </math>, and <math>
                  <latex>\Vect{x}_{\bot}\in V^{\bot}</latex>
               </math>. We have</para.body>
         </para>
         <math.array column="3">
            <row rowspan="1">
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>0</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>=	</latex>
                  </math>
                  <companion>
                     <info>
                        <info.caption>
                           <caption>Why is this so?</caption>
                        </info.caption>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>This dot product vanishes because <math>
                                 <latex>\Vect{x}\in V^{\bot\bot}</latex>
                              </math>.</para.body>
                        </para>
                     </info>
                  </companion>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>\DotPr{ \Vect{x} }{ \Vect{x}_{\bot} }</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
            </row>
            <row rowspan="1">
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle"/>
               <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>=</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>(\DotPr{ \Vect{x}_V }{ \Vect{x}_{\bot} })\ +\ (\DotPr{ \Vect{x}_{\bot} }{ \Vect{x}_{\bot} })</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
            </row>
            <row rowspan="1">
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle"/>
               <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>=</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>\DotPr{ \Vect{x}_{\bot} }{ \Vect{x}_{\bot} }</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
            </row>
         </math.array>
         <para>
            <para.body>This means that <math>
                  <latex>\Vect{x}_{\bot} = \Vect{0}</latex>
               </math> and, therefore, <math>
                  <latex>\Vect{x}=\Vect{x}_{V}\in V</latex>
               </math>.</para.body>
         </para>
         <caption>
            <math>
               <latex>V\subseteq S^{\bot\bot}</latex>
            </math>
         </caption>
         <para>
            <para.body>To see that <math>
                  <latex>V\subseteq S^{\bot\bot}</latex>
               </math>, consider a linear combination</para.body>
         </para>
         <math.array column="3">
            <row rowspan="1">
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>\Vect{x}</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>=</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>t_1 \Vect{s}_1 + \cdots + t_k \Vect{s}_k</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
            </row>
         </math.array>
         <para>
            <para.body>of <math>
                  <latex>S</latex>
               </math>. We need to show that <math>
                  <latex>\Vect{x}\in S^{\bot\bot}</latex>
               </math>. So let <math>
                  <latex>\Vect{z}\in S^{\bot}</latex>
               </math>. We need to show that <math>
                  <latex>\DotPr{ \Vect{x} }{ \Vect{z} } = 0</latex>
               </math>. So we compute</para.body>
         </para>
         <math.array column="3">
            <row rowspan="1">
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>\DotPr{ \Vect{x} }{ \Vect{z} }</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>=</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>\DotPr{ (t_1 \Vect{s}_1 +\cdots + t_k \Vect{s}_k) }{ \Vect{z} }</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
            </row>
            <row rowspan="1">
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle"/>
               <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>=</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>t_1(\DotPr{ \Vect{s}_1 }{ \Vect{z} }) + \cdots + t_k(\DotPr{ \Vect{s}_k }{ \Vect{z} })</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
            </row>
            <row rowspan="1">
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle"/>
               <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>=	</latex>
                  </math>
                  <companion>
                     <info>
                        <info.caption>
                           <caption>Why is this true?</caption>
                        </info.caption>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>Recall: <math>
                                 <latex>\Vect{z}\in S^{\bot}</latex>
                              </math>. So it is perpendicular to each of the vectors  <math>
                                 <latex>\Vect{s}_1</latex>
                              </math>, ... , <math>
                                 <latex>\Vect{s}_k</latex>
                              </math>.</para.body>
                        </para>
                     </info>
                  </companion>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>0</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
            </row>
         </math.array>
         <para>
            <para.body>This means that <math>
                  <latex>\Vect{x}\in S^{\bot\bot}</latex>
               </math> as required. – This completes the proof.</para.body>
         </para>
      </proof.block>
   </proof>
</theorem>
